						<summary>

						<p>Slab containing the image of a man attacking a tiger in the Vīrabhadra temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to the 15th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>This hero-stone inscription records that a certain Vīraya, son of Kannāṭi Kaṁnama-reḍḍi attacked a tiger and died.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">Inscriptions of Andhra Pradesh:</hi> Cuddapah District, Part II, No. 23.]</p>						

